      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): preserve long streaming replies",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Keep oversized Feishu final replies off the streaming-card path when they exceed the configured text chunk limit, including auto-mode markdown/code-block/table replies.\n- Discard any active streaming preview before delivering oversized final replies through the existing chunked message/static-card send path.\n- Add focused coverage for oversized plain and markdown final replies plus partial-preview cleanup.\n\nFixes #88631.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.test.ts` (66 tests)\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.ts extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main`\n- One-shot local Feishu-compatible HTTP proof harness using the real dispatcher, real chunker, real `sendMessageFeishu`/`sendStructuredCardFeishu`, and the real Lark SDK `Client.im.message.create` request path.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Feishu streaming no longer routes oversized plain or auto markdown/table/code-block final replies into streaming CardKit content that can exceed CardKit element limits.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout with a one-shot Feishu-compatible HTTP endpoint. The proof exercised `extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.ts`, `extensions/feishu/src/send.ts`, `extensions/feishu/src/client.ts`, `extensions/feishu/src/streaming-card.ts`, and the installed `@larksuiteoapi/node-sdk` client request path. This is real OpenClaw/Lark SDK code-path proof, not a mocked unit test and not a live Feishu tenant.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran the one-shot Node proof harness after the predicate fix, then reran the focused Vitest file and formatting/diff checks listed above.\n\nEvidence after fix: Plain oversized final with no partial preview produced 3 post chunks (`10,10,3`) and `cardkit_calls=0`. Plain oversized final after an active partial preview logged streaming start, `DELETE /open-apis/im/v1/messages/om_3`, then the same three post chunks. Oversized markdown/code-block final with no partial preview produced `interactive_create_calls=8` static card sends and `cardkit_calls=0`.\n\nObserved result after fix: Oversized plain final text is delivered as chunked Feishu post messages, while oversized markdown/code-block final text is delivered as chunked static interactive cards. Neither path closes the final answer through a streaming CardKit card; existing partial previews are explicitly discarded before final chunked delivery.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live Feishu tenant/CardKit API call was not run; this checkout has no configured Feishu/Lark app credentials or target, and repo search found no Feishu secret-backed live lane.\n",
        "branch": "codex/fix-feishu-card-truncation-88631",
