        "title": "[codex] Read exact X posts via FxTwitter",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add a key-free FxTwitter exact-post reader for public X/Twitter status URLs and numeric status IDs.\n- Route exact post references through FxTwitter before falling back to xAI-backed broader `x_search`.\n- Keep generic X search on the existing xAI auth path and update docs/tests/build guards for the new behavior.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** OpenClaw can read an exact public X/Twitter status URL through `x_search` without requiring an xAI API key for that exact post read.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local macOS OpenClaw Gateway/Dashboard, built from this patch, restarted under LaunchAgent, listening on `127.0.0.1:18789` with the promoted runtime snapshot.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Built OpenClaw, restarted the Gateway, verified `openclaw gateway status --deep`, then invoked the live Gateway HTTP tool endpoint with `curl` against `x_search` using `https://x.com/jack/status/20`.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Copied live output from the real Gateway invocation:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"provider\": \"fxtwitter\",\n  \"mode\": \"exact_post\",\n  \"statusId\": \"20\",\n  \"hasExpectedText\": true\n}\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The live Gateway returned `provider=fxtwitter`, `mode=exact_post`, `statusId=20`, and confirmed the expected post text was present (`just setting up my twttr`). This proves the exact-post path used FxTwitter and worked on a real running OpenClaw setup.\n- **What was not tested:** No known gaps for the exact public post-read path. Broader xAI-backed generic X search remains covered by targeted tests and still requires xAI auth.\n\n## Verification\n- `OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm check:changed`\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm test src/infra/tsdown-config.test.ts test/scripts/tsdown-build.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/startup-context.test.ts extensions/xai/x-search.test.ts extensions/xai/plugin-registration.contract.test.ts src/plugins/tools.optional.test.ts src/plugins/manifest-registry.test.ts`\n- `NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=8192 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm build`\n",
